Step 1: Determine the revenue.  
• From the income statement, the Total Revenue is 2637011.03.

Step 2: Determine the average total assets.  
• The balance sheet provides the total assets at the beginning and end of the period:  
 - Initial Total Assets = 13000000.00  
 - End Total Assets = 14214117.02  
• Calculate the average total assets = (13000000.00 + 14214117.02) / 2 = 13607058.51

Step 3: Calculate the Total Asset Turnover Ratio.  
• The formula is: Total Asset Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Total Assets  
• Compute: 2637011.03 / 13607058.51 ≈ 0.194

Rounded to two decimal places, the Total Asset Turnover Ratio is 0.19.

Thus, the result is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Total Asset Turnover Ratio": "0.19"
  }
}
